{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"31af8316-ccda-4ed6-9e51-cbb7dd64b619","content":"The directory is empty — there's no existing project here. No worries, I can show you exactly how to convert your page and catch errors at build time.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage`, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**What changed:** Only one line — the addition of `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`. All existing `{Binding …}` expressions are now compiled against the ViewModel's type at build time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. They're on by default** — once `x:DataType` is present, the XAML compiler resolves every `{Binding}` path. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\n**2. Ensure compilation is enabled** in your `.csproj` (it is by default for .NET MAUI, but verify):\n\n```xml\n<MauiXamlC>true</MauiXamlC>\n```\n\n**3. Opt out selectively** — if a binding intentionally targets a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate` for a collection item), scope a new `x:DataType`:\n\n```xml\n<CollectionView ItemsSource=\"{Binding Items}\">\n    <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n        <DataTemplate x:DataType=\"vm:ItemViewModel\">\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n        </DataTemplate>\n    </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n</CollectionView>\n```\n\nOr disable compilation for one binding with `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"`.\n\n**Key benefits:**\n| | Interpreted | Compiled (`x:DataType`) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Typo in property name | Silent runtime fail | **Build error** |\n| Wrong property type | Runtime exception | **Build error** |\n| Performance | Reflection-based | Direct call, ~8-20× faster |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e59108fa-0e20-4120-9422-9fce17be2af0","outputTokens":683},"id":"62f13105-1144-48d8-a827-2a55a6d188ec","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:57:30.163Z","parentId":"2954a961-add9-4a18-8dea-6f2f1699f861"}
